cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with video super-resolution for action recognition, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes two new methods for video super-resolution, which involves training neural networks, making it relevant to machine learning (MM) and deep learning (LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses two-stream networks, which are a popular method for action recognition and fall under the artificial intelligence (AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a siamese network, which is a type of neural network architecture commonly used in neural network embeddings (NE).
